Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop them
onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the
@mixed herbs{1%sachet}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrots{3%units}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel).
Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Pop the carrots onto one side of a large lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{} and the @honey{15%grams}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer on one half of the baking tray.

Roast on the middle shelf until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, finely chop the @chives{1%bunch}(finely chopped) (use
scissors if easier).

When the carrots have 15 mins of cooking time remaining, lay the
@basa fillets{2%units} onto the other half of the lined baking tray. Drizzle
with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and sprinkle over the
@lemon & herb seasoning{1%sachet}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked
> when opaque in the middle.

Bake the fish and carrots on the middle shelf of your oven for the remaining
~{10-15%minutes}.

A few mins before everything's ready, heat a small #saucepan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the @hollandaise sauce{100%grams} to the pan and heat whilst
stirring until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add half the chives to the sauce and stir to combine. Remove from the heat.

When ready, transfer the basa to your plates. Serve the roasted potatoes and
honeyed carrots alongside.

Spoon the hollandaise sauce over the basa fillets, then sprinkle over the
remaining chives to finish. Enjoy!